<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-12-01T02:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-12-01T02:00:00-05:00" n="706" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d706">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/12–149: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Peiping</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Clubb</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-12-01T15:00:00+08:00">December
                                    1, 1949—3 p. m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received December 1—1:50 p. m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>2149. French, British, Netherlands Consuls confirmed [they] received
                            likewise Chou’s statement mytel 2128, November 30, but Belgium and Italy
                            in non-receipt.</p>
                        <p>Acknowledged receipt letter addressed Wang Ping-nan personally yesterday,
                            informing him also had transmitted statement as requested that date.</p>
                        <p>Sent Department 2149; Department pass Shanghai 1247, Nanking 1197.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Clubb</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>